    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate NIH prediction accuracy within 15% acceptance criterion across all five operating points. RH < 1 confirmed for all COU operating conditions. The package is accepted for regulatory submission supporting the Class II CPB device 510(k) clearance pathway. Note: aleatory uncertainty in the pressure-rise validation result was characterized qualitatively by the experimental team based on observed pump-to-pump dimensional variation; formal structured UQ was not linked to that result, which is considered acceptable given the secondary role of this validation activity relative to the primary NIH comparison.",
